# NOTE: This file is used by Netlify / Cloudflare Pages only.
# GitHub Pages IGNORES this file — it cannot set custom HTTP headers.
#
# What GitHub Pages provides natively:
#   Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=31556952  (always on for *.github.io)
#
# What we enforce via <meta> tags in every HTML file instead:
#   <meta name="referrer" content="no-referrer">
#
# What CANNOT be set on GitHub Pages (server-header-only):
#   X-Content-Type-Options, Permissions-Policy
#   These require a reverse proxy (Cloudflare, Netlify, or a custom server)
#   if you need them enforced.

/*
  Referrer-Policy: no-referrer
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  Permissions-Policy: accelerometer=(), camera=(), geolocation=(), gyroscope=(), magnetometer=(), microphone=(), payment=(), usb=()
  Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=31536000; includeSubDomains; preload